PRESS CONFERENCE REGARDING COLIN POWELL -- ACU</title></head><body>
<center><h3>LEADERS OF THE CONSERVATIVE MOVEMENT TO HOLD
PRESS CONFERENCE REGARDING COLIN POWELL<br></h3>
<h4>DAVID KEENE, PAUL WEYRICH, AND OTHERS TO DISCUSS POWELL BID</h4> 
<P><i>October 30, 1995</i>
</center>
<br>    

<P>
<font size="-1">CONTACT: Cliff Johnson
<BR>Craig Shirley & Associstes
<BR>(703) 739-5920</font>
<hr>
<P> 
Washington, DC--Mr. <a href="/conservative/keene.html">David Keene</a>, Chairman of  the American Conservative Union, and Mr. Paul Weyrich, President of the Free Congress Foundation, along with other leaders of the conservative movement will hold a press conference on Thursday, November 2nd, regarding the possible GOP Presidential nomination bid of General Colin Powell.
<p>
"With the increasing media attention on Colin Powell and his political aspirations, it is important that the conservative movement address the prospect of a Powell candidacy," Keene said.
<p>
Keene will be joined by conservative movement leader Paul Weyrich, President of the Free Congress Foundalion, at the press conference to be held at 3:00pm on Thursday, November 2nd, in the First Amendment Room of the National Press Club.
<p><ul>
WHO:  David Keene, Chairman of the Amencan Conservative Union; Paul Weyricb, President of the Free Congress Foundation; and other Conservative leaders
<p>
WHAT: Press conference announcing the position of the conservative movement on a Colin Powell presidential bid.
<p>
WHEN: 3:00pm on Thursday, November 2, 1995
<p>
WHERE: First Ameninent Room in the NationaI Press Club, 529 14th Street, NW
</ul><p>
For more information on the American Conservative Union, the Free Congress Foundation, the press conference, or to schedule an interview with either David Keene, Chairman of the ACU, or Paul Weyrich, President of the Free Congress Foundation, please contact Cliff Johnson of Craig Shirley & Associates at (703) 739-5920.<P><center>[ <a href="/conservative/welcome.html">ACU Home</a> ]</center>
