<title>Heritage President Feulner Named Kamp's Campaign Counsellor - Heritage PR</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg"><center>
<img src="/heritage/news.gif" height=111 width=576 alt="The Heritage Foundation News">
<h2>HERITAGE PRESIDENT FEULNER NAMED 
KEMP'S CAMPAIGN COUNSELLOR</h2></center>


<b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
CONTACT: Herb Berkowitz,
Vice President, Heritage Public Relations
<p>


	WASHINGTON, Aug. 20, 1996</b> - Heritage Foundation President <a href="/heritage/staff/feulner.html">Edwin J. Feulner Jr.</a> will take a leave of absence to become The Counsellor to Republican Vice Presidential candidate Jack Kemp, effective Aug. 21, the chairman of the prominent think tank announced today. Heritage Chairman David R. Brown said Feulner will work for Kemp for the duration of the campaign.
<p>
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;	Kemp, a former Buffalo, N.Y., congressman and Secretary of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) during the Bush administration, had been a <a href="/heritage/staff/kemp.htm">distinguished fellow</a> at The Heritage Foundation and co-founder of <a href="/empower">Empower America</a> until his selection as Bob Dole's running mate at last week's Republican convention in San Diego.
<p>
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;	Feulner, president of The Heritage Foundation since 1977, is a long-time friend and confidante of Kemp. He served as vice chairman of the National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform (popularly known as the <a href="/taxcom">Kemp Commission</a>) from May 1995 to March 1996. Prior to joining Heritage he was director of the Republican Study Committee in the House of Representatives.
<p>
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;	A native of Chicago, the 55-year-old Feulner is a graduate of Regis College, Denver. He has an MBA from the University of Pennsylvania's Wharton School and a Ph.D. from the University of Edinburgh, Scotland.
	<p>
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; 
He and his wife Linda reside in Alexandria, Va.
<p>
<center>[ <a href="/heritage/">The Heritage Foundation</a> | <a href="/townhall/media_services/welcome.html.cgi">Press Release Index</a> ]
</center></body></html>
