<center>
<h2>Bradley, White to Attend Aspen Summit '96</h2>
</center>
<br>
Senator Bill Bradley (D-NJ) and Representative Rick White (R-WA) will be among the participants at the Aspen Summit this August 5-6, The Progress & Freedom Foundation announced today. The Summit will explore whether America's future in the digital age will be one of progress or decay.
<p>
White, who is chairman of the Congressional Internet Caucus, and Bradley, who recently completed a tour promoting his new book <i>Time Present, Time Past</i>, will be among the more than 30 participants at the Sumrnit. Also attending will be author Alvin Toffler, PBS commentator David Gergen, ACLU president Nadine Strossen, author George Gilder, John Gage of Sun Microsystems, and author David Gelemter.
<p>
"A recurring theme in this election year is the insecurity Arnericans feel about their future," said Foundation president Jeffrey A. Eisenach. "The Summit will examine how America can best cope with the transition to a new society - how to make the transition less painful and more productive for all Americans.
<p>
The Summit, to be held at the Ritz-Carlton Hotel in Aspen, Colo., will also feature a debate on whether the growth of the Internet is a "Leading Cultural Indicator of Progress." Participants will include Edwin Diamond and Stephen Bates, authors of "Smash the Internet" (<i>WeeSdy Standard</i>, Oct. 30, 1995), G.A. (Jay) Keyworth, former Science Advisor to President Reagan, and Esther Dyson, president of EDventure Holdings.
<p>
Four working groups at the Summit will explore what government policies should be pursued.to ensure continued progress tosward a better future the the digital age. Former FCC Commissioner Dennis Patrick will highlight a session on reglulatory convergence and Shira Perlmutter, Associate Register for International Affairs and Policy at the Copyright Office, will highlight a session on intellectual property.
<p>
A private, non-profit, non-partisan idea center established in 1993, The Progress & Freedom Foundation aims to create a positive vision of the future founded in the
historic principles of the American idea.
